<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Try (I said try =P) and use the terrain/other players to your advantage.  Try and flank the enemy, use trees, hide behind Paladins/Armsmen, whatever it takes not to get seen.  On Bedevere there are usually 5 Bards for every Sorc on the battlefield (no, I'm not exaggerating) so it's really important to stay out of sight if you can.  There's really nothing you can do to be 100% successful other than staying out of the frontier so be patient if some nights you get owned a lot.  Albion needs their Sorcs desparately; just try and use terrain and other tactics to give yourself opportunities to toss AE Mez.
</FONT>
